column8: You're strong, short one. And just as bull-headed as I.
If you're most certain, Theseus, then I'm most certain. How about I crush him. <Snort> Haven't crushed the life from something in ages.
You watch your mouth, short one.  <Snort> You address the bull-slayer! The greatest king of Athens, Theseus! And you are far from home, here in Elysium.
Enough discussion, Theseus. You give him opportunity to strike, when I could strike him down right here and now! You need but give the signal, and I'll break his every bone. <Snort>
It is my pleasure to oblige you, king.
Good. Then let us crush the life from him, together, king.
So much for a fair fight.
The Champion and I will reign forever.
It will take you more than that to vanquish me.
I will be waiting for you to return.
May this defeat fill you with vengeful fury.
This is the fate of those who challenge me.
Return to the bowels of hell, short one.
